Q.1 Case study on cyber security risk management Explain the control architecture and supporting processes?" [15M]
Answer (Exam Format):
Objective: Understand cyber security risk management and its control architecture.
Case Study Example:
•	Company: A fintech startup handling digital payments.
•	Risk: Unauthorized access, data breaches, malware attacks.
•	Goal: Implement a risk management framework.
Control Architecture:
1.	Preventive Controls:
•	Firewalls and antivirus software
•	Access controls (Role-based access)
•	Encryption of sensitive data
2.	Detective Controls:
•	Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS)
•	Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)
•	Regular audits and monitoring
3.	Corrective Controls:
•	Patch management and software updates
•	Incident response procedures
•	Backup and recovery plans
Supporting Processes:
1.	Risk Assessment: Identify assets, vulnerabilities, and threats.
2.	Risk Analysis: Evaluate impact and likelihood of risks.
3.	Risk Mitigation: Apply appropriate controls (technical, administrative).
4.	Monitoring & Review: Continuous evaluation of risks and controls.
Observation / Conclusion:
•	Cybersecurity risk management ensures confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data.
•	Regular updates and monitoring are critical in fintech environments to prevent losses and maintain trust.
