Q.1 Security in CI/CD and DevSecOps [15M]
(a) How to Implement Security in a CI/CD Pipeline [5M]
Answer:
•	CI/CD (Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment) pipelines automate building, testing, and deploying software. Security can be integrated at every stage to prevent vulnerabilities.
Steps to Implement Security:
1.	Code Analysis:
•	Use Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tools to detect vulnerabilities in code during development.
2.	Dependency Scanning:
•	Check third-party libraries for known vulnerabilities using tools like OWASP Dependency-Check.
3.	Container Security:
•	Scan Docker images for vulnerabilities before deployment.
4.	Secrets Management:
•	Protect API keys, passwords, and certificates using secure vaults.
5.	Automated Testing:
•	Run Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST) in staging environments.
6.	Monitoring and Logging:
•	Integrate real-time monitoring to detect anomalous behavior after deployment.
7.	Policy Enforcement:
•	Ensure security policies are automatically applied before any release.
